task.summary: Default task
Just trying to get started
Main image display locate by id search and show right hand list jump to selected search result start of rank display
Main image display locate by id search and show right hand list jump to selected search result start of rank display

Add LESS and loading GIF
Style sheets are now compiled from LESS. Loading GIF runs while AJAX calls are in flight

Rank list
Bootstrap templates

JQuery layout
Integrate jQuery layout as replacement for w2ui. Get header for search/rank list working

Rank navigation buttons
Nav rank shows and search hides up and down buttons for the rank list. North and east panes open and close, but do not resize.

Gauge and sorted reviews
Completed gauge with AmCharts (boo Google Visualization) Reviews are now sorted by popularity. Jump to BGG

Videos
Display videos in thumbed order Show thumbnails and links Jump to additional videos on bgg game page

Back and Forward
Implement control that allows you to look at the previous game you loaded or, if you have already backed up, the next one. The list grows without end unlike the forward and back browser buttons. If you back up and then go forward, it does not remove your prior forward items. That is, if I get item1 and them item2, thenI back up to item1, and then get item3, forward will still be possible and will go to item2.

Google Gauge
Replace AmCharts with Google visualization gauge Encapsulate gauge drawing to a separate class * only expose one method to update the difficulty * other methods are private
Refactor gi to a class called GameInfo

Related Items
* Hover over tag shows related items in a dropdown list. * Relations with multiple objects show in a submenu * Items are clickable * Game items jump to target game * Groups or families show list of items in right hand pane

Related People
* Refactor list calls in the main page to parameterized calls to a single function * Support pagination for family lists as well as for rank lists * Support showing lists for designers and artists (aka people) * Remove comments from srchres.html * Attempt to fix video list layout issue: probably didn't work.

Refactor for pub-sub
* Create classes for each pane, header, main and list * Establish messages for each pane: - header can update contents of each edit, update status message and show loading gif - main can set the game information - list can show rank, search or family/person list * Split gigetter into three classes - gameinfo.js gets game related information - gamelist.js gets list related info - accessutil.js has common methods for manipulating returned text * index.html now only creates the layout and pane classes and provides support for layout manipulation requests * No more global variables other than App. (Except for relateditemmap)

Pure,js (for some things) and game history navigation
* Added game history status in south pane * Pure.js for game information, although not for search lists * Can't do pure for the related items since the tree is too complex * Dropdown for history on forward and back (homegrown timer implementation) * Factored out display of lists so that the history dropdown could use the same code as the list pane

Bring back up in IntelliJ
Replace local includes with bower includes Replace xdproxy with PHP proxy from https://github.com/Esri/resource-proxy Fix boardgameprices.com search URL Modify slugging to remove articles and prepositions

Merge back popup charts for rating, difficulty and age.
Permit making a jquery object from a response by stripping out scripts
First implementation of rating history chart

FUrther ratings history improvements
Changed back from line to linechart Got tooltips working Progressive display.

Rating history speedup
Turns out templating, string replacement, they're all too slow, so I had to do something homegrown. Google visualizations DataView renders everything at the start so it doesn't get around the problem

Fast enough ratings history chart rendering
Who knew that most of the cost was in Date.toLocaleString()? Replace jquery.layout's failing addCloseBtn call with a manual call

Fast enough ratings history chart rendering
Who knew that most of the cost was in Date.toLocaleString()? Replace jquery.layout's failing addCloseBtn call with a manual call
Adjust ratings popup Protect against retrieving history in the future if the history isn't exactly one entry per day.
Add User collection listing Remove dead files

Added cool tooltips to lists. Redid collection implementation to support retrieving only one game so that I can tell if the current user owns the current game. Some level of protection and retry against history that comes back fucked up. Capture the current user, if one was set. A little JSHint cleanup.
Oopsie, forgot to delete a comma.

Game ownership mods: Traffic light to left of game name shows ownership status If you don't own it, it is red, green for own and yellow for want Ownership is for current user who is the last user whose collection was retrieved Click on traffic light for game you don't own to add it to your collection: Assumes that a blind request to bgg will just work because your credentials are stored in cookies., Start bolding owned games. Now quite finished Logo Swap order of preposition removal during slugging so that it happens first : Tzolk'in ==> tzolk Refactor centerpane.js so that each section is populated by its own function

Implement Hotness and help (in its barest form.) Hide the game ID Add retries to some of the game info requests. Add jquery-ajax-retry package. Protect against bad use of URI Factor out common code for search and hotness

Implement Hotness and help (in its barest form.) Hide the game ID Add retries to some of the game info requests. Add jquery-ajax-retry package. Protect against bad use of URI Factor out common code for search and hotness

Implement AjaxTracker Modularize it so that it can be hung off of anything Make it accessible as a modal dialog off of the headerpane
Start retrieving info from xmlapi as well as xmlapi2 since it provides some additional interesting information. It properly parses the response and replicates the info available for api2. Don't yet have the mappings for the additional related items since I no longer understand what I did there.
Stub out the rating history since it looks like BGG don't like what I did there.
Implement sorting for family lists Add support for subdomains, publishers, honors lists
